.SH "NAME"
dvd_eject \- eject or close an optical device tray
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
\fBdvd_eject\fP [\fIOPTIONS\fP] [\fIDEVICE\fP]
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
Use FreeBSD\(cqs \fIcdcontrol\fP program to eject or close an optical tray, adding DVD\-specific options.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.sp
\fB\-t\fP
Close tray instead of opening.
.sp
\fB\-d\fP
Display DVD id after closing tray using dvd_info.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.sp
dvd_backup(1), dvd_copy(1), dvd_drive_status(1), dvd_info(1), dvd_player(1), dvd_rip(1), dvd_trip(1)
